::Shadow Wing::

She looked away from Lunarpine for a moment.  She took off in flight 
and flew off into the trees.  She returned a few moments later with a 
blue jay in her talons. She perched back at the same low branch that 
she was on moments ago.  "How about this instead of a rock?" She let 
go of the bird and let it fall near Lunarpine.
"One must be strong in order to fight."
She smiled and waited for him to eat the bird and then continue with 
the game.  She really wanted to learn how to fight in hand to hand 
combat, but not quite like this. But for now, this would suffice.
